# UI Component Reuse And Product Parity

- Treat existing reusable components as the first choice for UI work. Before adding a new component or styling pattern, look for an existing component, shared package, or local pattern to extend.
- For admin web UI, prefer shadcn-vue components once the shadcn setup exists. Keep wrappers thin and reusable instead of placing one-off markup in pages.
- Any user-facing feature added or changed in admin must be considered for both mobile apps, and any user-facing mobile feature must be considered for admin. Keep features the same across admin and mobile as much as the platform allows.
- If a feature cannot be visible or equivalent in both admin and mobile, document the reason in the implementation notes or ask for product direction before proceeding.
